If I could give NO STARS, I would. Horrible service. I had made an order for delivery. I ordered pork fried rice and chicken lo mein. The delivery person calls me from my hotel lobby DEMANDING I come down to get the order. I get down there to collect my order and he takes off with my receipt. I called the restaurant to get the order rectified and they argue with me telling me I didn't order the lo mein, even though I'm looking at my Eat24 app and the digital receipt. I then asked what are they going to do to fix the problem - silence. I asked again and then stated if they weren't going to fix the problem, I was going to call my credit card company. They literally said "okay, whatever" and hung up on me.  I would NOT recommend this place at all based on poor service. Sad really since the pork fried rice is great.

I walk by this place every day on the way to work, and it's standard, tasty american Chinese food.  The first time was great. I was having a 15-person dinner party one night and knew wanted Chinese take out. I walked in after work and talked with Sally, at the cash register. She was awesome. I ordered 3-4 servings of 6 or so dishes because the party platter would have just been too much food and too expensive.  Sally worked with me to make sure all the food was ready on time, the portions would be enough for the party, and that it was in my budget.  When i came to pick up, she was meticulous, rechecking each item from the other and any of the little extras that came with it. The food was exactly what we needed for the party, and we even had leftovers. She was packing everything fresh from the wok and it was great!  The next time i ate from here, I ordered delivery. The food was just as good.  My only two critiques-- some of the veggie dishes have thick sauces, and the fried chicken dishes do have a lot of breading. But when you're looking for something starchy, carby, saucy, it hits the spot.
We ordered takeout for a large group and had a bad experience. The lo mein was okay, but everything else was a soggy, greasy overcooked mess. Would not eat again.

The food was rotten.  Literally rotten, they served spoiled food.  The food quality was also abysmal, I could barely find the meat underneath the soggy breading and all the sauces were nearly water, but I'm pretty sure that next to the spoiled food that nothing else really matters.  I just looked up the inspection reports, in July 2013 they were shut down due to 19 violations.

Original: 8 June 2010 I just finished eating their General Tso's -- among the best I've had in the DC/MD area.  Makes me glad I just moved in a block away!  Update: 17 Sept 2010 The last two times I've gone, the General Tso's has been horrid... the sauce & exterior of the chicken was great; but inside it seems dearly undercooked.  I may try it one more time just to make sure... but 3 strikes and that'll be it.
